[DhtmlXQ_comment0]op ldz c0102020301 no backup no reckless advancement||While trying to develop your chess pieces is the golden rule to follow in the opening, it must be done with care. When you try to occupy an  intersection, you must consider the following things:||a) are there available backup?||b) will it be beneficial to your side as a whole?[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment6]Red and black started the game with a pawn versus pawn opening.||Black's horse is called the trailblazer horse or 先锋马 in chinese.[/DhtmlXQ_comment6]
[DhtmlXQ_comment13]And black's horse would be threatened.||In the opening stages, the horse can be easily compromised because of the way it moves. The presence of numerous chess pieces on the board would also mean that it can be restricted.||That is why, in the opening stages, the potential and function of the horse is often limited, in comparison to the chariot and cannon.||Therefore, it is unwise to charge a horse into enemy territory early. If the chance does arise, the horse should be advanced only with adequate and timely backup.[/DhtmlXQ_comment13]
[DhtmlXQ_comment1_13]Red would have the obvious advantage.[/DhtmlXQ_comment1_13]
